Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Unsupervised learning: Clustering", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7778228768683653`*^9, 3.7778228878122883`*^9}, {
  3.8146949835077934`*^9, 
  3.8146949906712666`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9c73362f-08d6-49a1-8eed-\
b15e9e92b9df"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Given a set of data, the aim of data clustering is to identify groups (or \
clusters) of data, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["G", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["G", "2"], ",", "...", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["G", "K"]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bf5db000-ef7b-48db-bd53-9336221e38e6"],
 ", such that objects within a cluster are similar to other objects in the \
same cluster and are quite distinct to objects in different clusters. \n\n\
Data clustering is also called simply clustering, cluster analysis, \
segmentation analysis or taxonomy analysis.\n\nClustering differs from \
classification in the sense that the input data used for clustering are \
unlabelled, i.e. the aim is to infer classes instead of defining them using \
training data.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  GraphicsBox[
   TagBox[RasterBox[CompressedData["
