Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Normalisation of the data", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7811973331017647`*^9, 
  3.781197339218606*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d3a0cdd1-aef2-443c-ab12-\
9fcbf4f44749"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Since clustering methods use distance measures to quantify the similarity \
of data points, it is important to standardize data for clustering. This is \
done in the same way as explained before for the K Nearest Neighbours (KNN) \
classification method.",
 StyleBox[" FindClusters", "CodeText"],
 " standardizes the data automatically."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7811973434096146`*^9, 
  3.781197491355756*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9db55754-02b2-4147-a70a-\
63f120ab9b49"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["How to choose K for KMC?", "Section"]], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7791770979606533`*^9, 3.7791771091268463`*^9}, {
  3.8146948635380154`*^9, 3.8146948655097036`*^9}, {3.8146949067758327`*^9, 
  3.8146949151333437`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ebe69a8a-9bde-4945-8bde-\
11a41563340a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the example considered above, we set ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 2 because, in fact, we knew that the data consisted of two clusters. In \
general, however, we will not know a reasonable value of ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". There are several ways to find a reasonable value of ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Here, we describe the scree plot which is typically effective and it is \
relatively easy to understand and implement."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779178443765131*^9, 3.779178606037943*^9}, {
   3.779178664166162*^9, 3.7791786944556713`*^9}, 
   3.7811886991451*^9},ExpressionUUID->"5a6e0772-92f9-479a-a5e7-05da91fa7240"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Scree plot", "Section"]], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778511481117416*^9, 3.778511483645108*^9}, {
  3.778512267970303*^9, 3.7785122744286537`*^9}, {3.7785123081730137`*^9, 
  3.778512310108622*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fb901784-9aab-46d5-ae2a-\
19b43582f679"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Adding up the squared distances of each point to the centre of the nearest \
cluster gives a measure of total distance within a cluster, dispersion or \
error.\n\nLet ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["G", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bc56c1fa-ede2-4ab8-945a-a6830120e0d7"],
 " be the ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "-th cluster and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["c",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fbe7aa0d-0162-4ef8-82c9-59fc8014d935"],
 " its centre. The error of points within ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["G", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "46b23f2b-61c4-4475-8f63-4855fefc3a1a"],
 " is given by the sum of the square the distance of each data point in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["G", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d7cb9db0-e359-4ce2-94b9-cd4a445e431c"],
 " to the centre of the cluster:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["Error", 
     RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]], "="}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "26c6deb3-57b2-4a21-b20b-f8b98ea6a4fc"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{"i", "\[Element]", 
      SubscriptBox["G", "k"]}]], 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["d", "2"], "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["x",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       RowBox[{"(", "i", ")"}]], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["c",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ce4c0943-bda9-4c94-95e6-37a73a6cde1e"],
 "\n\nThe total error is then the sum of errors for each cluster:\n\nError = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
      RowBox[{"k", "=", "1"}], "K"], 
     SuperscriptBox["Error", 
      RowBox[{"(", "k", ")"}]]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["Error", 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["Error", 
        RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]], "+"}], "..."}], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["Error", 
      RowBox[{"(", "K", ")"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1d6efaf9-92a9-42e4-b524-81e98f50dded"],
 "\n\nThe error decays with the number of clusters, ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". \n\nTo see this, consider the extreme case with one cluster per point \
(i.e. ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "). In this case, the error is zero because the centre of each cluster \
coincides with the point!\n\n",
 StyleBox["The scree plot is the plot of the error vs. ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["K",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779180402902124*^9, 3.77918042613503*^9}, {
   3.779180531011992*^9, 3.779180693431099*^9}, {3.779180855812312*^9, 
   3.779180875333638*^9}, {3.779180931334518*^9, 3.779180971636086*^9}, {
   3.779181074116452*^9, 3.779181077107147*^9}, {3.779181146484296*^9, 
   3.779181185011269*^9}, {3.779181230291645*^9, 3.779181360868333*^9}, {
   3.779181506679414*^9, 3.779181687348873*^9}, {3.779181793556189*^9, 
   3.779181882899935*^9}, {3.779183435506765*^9, 3.779183467204173*^9}, {
   3.779183542553069*^9, 3.77918362531619*^9}, {3.779183861204262*^9, 
   3.7791838808350983`*^9}, {3.779188225134761*^9, 3.7791882268143682`*^9}, {
   3.7791896538991747`*^9, 3.779189675240267*^9}, 3.781951518337185*^9, {
   3.7819519542335567`*^9, 3.78195199145391*^9}, {3.781952080072822*^9, 
   3.7819520804577913`*^9}, {3.7826618848798523`*^9, 
   3.782661886660681*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f3a6695f-af25-4fc2-a63a-\
9b3d30c95e48"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Example", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779182079202883*^9, 
  3.77918208821017*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eabf226b-cbde-4bd0-a6fd-\
